member.example:
This sample shows how to call GetAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var client = new MeasurementMetadataSchemaFileInfoClient(credential);

Response response = await client.GetAsync("<measurementId>");

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("schemaFileName").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("schemaFileUri").ToString());

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the response payload.
Response Body:
Schema for MeasurementMetadataSchemaFileInfoBase: { schemaFileName: string, # Optional. schemaFileUri: string, # Required. }

